cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper deals with algorithms for determinisation and completion of finite tree automata, which are topics related to formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential applications of the algorithms in program analysis and verification, which could place it in cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper contains an experimental evaluation of the algorithm, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
